<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      metal:use-macro="here/main_template/macros/master"
      i18n:domain="upfront.classlist"
      lang="en">

<body>
    <metal:main fill-slot="main">

    <div id="content-core">

        <h1 i18n:translate="heading_import_learners">Import learners</h1>

        <p class="documentDescription">
           Here you can import learners via an Excel spreadsheet.
        </p>
            
        <form name="form" action="." method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data"
                tal:attributes="action string:${here/absolute_url}/@@uploadClasslistSpreadsheet">
            <div class="labels">
                <div> 
                <label for="new_classlist_id" 
                    i18n:translate="label_create_new_class">
                    Class name:
                </label>
                </div> 
                <div> 
                    <label for="csv_file" i18n:translate="select_file">Use the learners in this file:</label>
                </div> 
                <div>&nbsp;</div>
            </div>

            <div class="edit_areas">
                <div>
                    <input type="text" name="new_classlist_id" class="required"
                            id="new_classlist_id"/>
                </div> 
               
                <div> 
                    <input type="file" id="csv_file" name="csv_file"/>
                </div> 
                <div> 
                    <br/>
                    <input class="context"
                        type="submit"
                        value="Import the learners"
                        name="submit"
                        i18n:attributes="value"/>
                        <!--tabindex=""
                        tal:attributes="tabindex tabindex/next;"
                        />-->

                    <input type="hidden" name="current_url"
                        tal:attributes="value here/absolute_url">
                </div> 
            </div>
                
        </form>
        <br/> 

        <div class="help_text">
            <h3>Required spreadsheet format:</h3>
            
            <ol>
                <li>
                    It must have only the following columns and in this sequence:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Learner Code</li>
                        <li>Full Name</li>
                        <li>Gender</li>
                        <li>Home Language</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                    No headers to columns, just the learner details
                </li>

                <li>
                    Valid values for Gender are 'Male' and 'Female'
                </li>

                <li>
                    Valid values for Home Language are:
                    <ul>
                        <li> Afrikaans </li>
                        <li> English </li>
                        <li> isiNdebele </li>
                        <li> isiXhosa </li>
                        <li> isiZulu </li>
                        <li> seSotho sa Lebowa </li>
                        <li> Sesotho </li>
                        <li> Setswana </li>
                        <li> siSwati </li>
                        <li> Tshivenda </li>
                        <li> Xitsonga </li>
                        <li> Unknown </li>
                        <li> Other </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    An example of a valid row in the spreadsheet would be:<br/>
                    1234 | Thabo Msimang | Male | isiXhosa
                </li>
                <li>
                    You can download an example of a valid class list import-spreadsheet here
                </li>
            </ol>
            <a href="#"
                tal:attributes="href string:${portal_url}/classlist.xls">Download an example class list here.</a>
        </div>

    </div>

    </metal:main>
</body>
</html>
